title: Brexit votes in the United Kingdom by social class 2016
summary: This grouped bar chart shows SOME LABEL on the Y-axis for 4 different Responses for 2 groups Remain, and Leave that are presented on the X-axis.
In Response Upper Working-Class (C2), Leave had the highest SOME LABEL 64.0 among the 2 groups and in Lower Working-Class (DE), Remain had the lowest SOME LABEL 36.0.
Among all the Responses, Leave had the highest SOME LABEL 64.0 in Response Upper Working-Class (C2) and lowest value 43.0 in Response Upper Middle-Class (AB).
There is a gap of 21.0 between the highest and lowest SOME LABEL found for Leave in Response Upper Working-Class (C2) and Upper Middle-Class (AB).
min_summary: This grouped bar chart shows SOME LABEL on the Y-axis for 4 different Responses for 2 groups Remain, and Leave that are presented on the X-axis.
Out of all 2 groups, Leave had the highest SOME LABEL in Response Upper Working-Class (C2) and Remain had the lowest SOME LABEL in Response Lower Working-Class (DE).

max_summary: This grouped bar chart shows SOME LABEL on the Y-axis for 4 different Responses for 2 groups Remain, and Leave that are presented on the X-axis.
Response Upper Working-Class (C2) had the maximum SOME LABEL among all 2 groups, and it was for Leave. The minimum SOME LABEL was observed in Response Lower Working-Class (DE) for Remain.
Among all the Responses, Leave had the highest SOME LABEL in Response Upper Working-Class (C2) and lowest SOME LABEL in Response Upper Middle-Class (AB).
The maximum SOME LABEL for Leave that was found in Response Upper Working-Class (C2) was 1.49 times larger than the minimum SOME LABEL observed in Response Upper Middle-Class (AB).
Out of all 2 groups, the highest gap between the maximum and minimum SOME LABEL was found in case of Remain.
On average, the Response Upper Middle-Class (AB) had the highest SOME LABEL for all 2 groups Remain, and Leave. Whereas Lower Working-Class (DE) had the lowest average SOME LABEL.
